`toList()` means [`Collectors.toList()`][1] with `java.util.stream.Collectors.toList` is being statically imported.

    import static java.util.stream.Collectors.toList;

[`Stream#collect`][2] expects a [`Collector`][3]

    &lt;R, A&gt; R collect(Collector&lt;? super T, A, R&gt; collector);

and [`Collectors.toList()`][1] returns a [`Collector`][3]

    public static &lt;T&gt; Collector&lt;T, ?, List&lt;T&gt;&gt; toList() { ... }


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/13/docs/api/java.base/java/util/stream/Collectors.html#toList()
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/13/docs/api/java.base/java/util/stream/Stream.html#collect(java.util.stream.Collector)
  [3]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/13/docs/api/java.base/java/util/stream/Collector.html

